explanation: This problem can be solved using dynamic programming. We create a 2D array dp where dp[i][j] represents the minimum number of turns needed to print the substring s[i...j]. We fill up the dp array in a bottom-up manner. If the characters at the start and end of the substring are the same, we don't need to print anything, so we just copy the value from the top-left cell. If the characters are different, we need to print the character at the start and then recursively call the function for the remaining substring. The minimum number of turns is the minimum of these two cases.

